No, definitely not.

270
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:01,385
Someone else did it,
and he's in prison now.

271
00:21:01,468 --> 00:21:04,346
A cop tried to frame her back then,
got punished

272
00:21:04,429 --> 00:21:06,181
and has held a grudge ever since.

273
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:07,683
That cop is

274
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:09,226
Park Dae-ho?

275
00:21:09,685 --> 00:21:10,686
Yes.

276
00:21:13,605 --> 00:21:16,149
So, does that mean
Ah-jin almost got arrested?

277
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:20,237
What were you doing
while all that happened to her?

278
00:21:21,238 --> 00:21:23,156
There was nothing I could do then.

279
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:27,286
Don't tell me
you're also suspecting her.

280
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:30,163
She was cleared without a charge

281
00:21:30,247 --> 00:21:32,040
and there hasn't been
a problem since.

282
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:34,626
She'll be in trouble
if the press gets wind of this now.

283
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:36,920
And that cop is nasty.

284
00:21:37,212 --> 00:21:38,672
Who knows what he might try?

285
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:46,096
I only saw her on TV

286
00:21:47,014 --> 00:21:48,765
so I thought she was doing fine.

287
00:21:52,269 --> 00:21:53,312
Tell me what to do.

288
00:21:54,229 --> 00:21:55,397
I'll help.

289
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,198
How is it going with Lieutenant Park?

290
00:22:06,074 --> 00:22:07,200
I'm still on it.

291
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:10,037
I have most of his movements
mapped out.

292
00:22:11,413 --> 00:22:14,708
He'll go wild
if you poke him carelessly.

293
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:16,710
Do it right.

294
00:22:17,252 --> 00:22:19,463
Don't worry. We've got help.

295
00:22:19,546 --> 00:22:20,672
Help?

296
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:21,965
Open the door.

297
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:26,428
Open it!

298
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:28,388
You'll be glad to see him, too.

299
00:22:34,561 --> 00:22:36,271
Took you long enough.

300
00:22:36,355 --> 00:22:38,899
Do you know how long I waited
out here because of you?

301
00:22:38,982 --> 00:22:40,984
I almost froze to death for beer.

302
00:22:41,068 --> 00:22:43,362
Well, you back now, so say hi.

303
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:46,073
But it's so late. Say hi to who?

304
00:22:55,290 --> 00:22:57,459
It's been a long time, Jae-oh.

305
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,465
You scared me.

306
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:11,848
I got out last December.

307
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:14,768
I served four full years.

308
00:23:15,811 --> 00:23:17,437
What do you do now?

309
00:23:18,980 --> 00:23:20,565
Well...

310
00:23:20,649 --> 00:23:25,112
I just take action
when the office gives me an order.

311
00:23:25,487 --> 00:23:29,241
Deliveries, transfers, transport...

312
00:23:29,324 --> 00:23:30,617
All kinds of stuff.

313
00:23:36,498 --> 00:23:37,499
DIRECT SOLUTION

314
00:23:37,582 --> 00:23:39,042
And I do background checks.

315
00:23:40,168 --> 00:23:43,046
And some odd jobs
when there's nothing else.

316
00:23:47,843 --> 00:23:48,844
Hey.

317
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:53,306
I thought you'd ignore me
now that you're a celebrity.

318
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:54,724
You're pretty loyal.

319
00:23:57,561 --> 00:23:58,728
Back off.

320
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:00,730
No.

321
00:24:02,858 --> 00:24:06,153
I want a good look at my friend.
What's wrong with that?

322
00:24:08,155 --> 00:24:09,156
"Friend"?

323
00:24:10,198 --> 00:24:12,200
Since when were you my friend?

324
00:24:13,618 --> 00:24:15,203
You're right.

325
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,122
Boss?

326
00:24:19,749 --> 00:24:22,669
Make time for me sometime.
The boss will buy you dinner.

327
00:24:22,752 --> 00:24:24,004
Are you for real?

328
00:24:24,379 --> 00:24:27,507
Then I'm asking
for a very expensive meal.

329
00:24:27,924 --> 00:24:29,134
Like what?

330
00:24:31,386 --> 00:24:32,512
Trouble pasta.

331
00:24:33,305 --> 00:24:35,557
You mean "truffle," idiot.

332
00:24:36,057 --> 00:24:37,559
That stuff is crazy expensive.

333
00:24:38,768 --> 00:24:41,021
- Name it. It's on me.
- More?

334
00:24:41,104 --> 00:24:42,856
- What else?
- Chuck flap tail?

335
00:24:42,939 --> 00:24:44,357
Chuck flap tail?

336
00:24:44,816 --> 00:24:46,067
Burgers, pizza.

337
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,736
- That's what you want?
- Jjajangmyeon.

338
00:24:48,487 --> 00:24:49,738
- And this.
- What is that?

339
00:24:49,821 --> 00:24:52,324
- You know, they drop it like this.
- What?

340
00:25:28,985 --> 00:25:30,070
Get in.

341
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:39,454
What's this?

342
00:25:39,538 --> 00:25:40,664
It's for you.

343
00:25:41,164 --> 00:25:42,249
It's a burner phone.

344
00:25:43,291 --> 00:25:44,501
Drive safely, sir!

345
00:26:01,518 --> 00:26:02,519
Hey.

346
00:26:03,562 --> 00:26:04,896
Come to think of it

347
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,274
you didn't want me
to talk to you in school.

348
00:26:07,983 --> 00:26:09,442
Didn't you hate me back then?

349
00:26:10,235 --> 00:26:11,736
I still do.

350
00:26:17,284 --> 00:26:19,202
Then why did you let me see her?

351
00:26:21,955 --> 00:26:23,331
Don't you like Ah-jin?

352
00:26:25,917 --> 00:26:27,002
Does it look like it?

353
00:26:28,044 --> 00:26:29,671
Wow, you're serious.

354
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:31,256
That pisses me off.

355
00:26:31,673 --> 00:26:34,718
I just want her to live
an ordinary life.

356
00:26:35,427 --> 00:26:36,886
That's why I need you.

357
00:26:38,305 --> 00:26:41,099
Because she's more likely to live
a normal life

358
00:26:42,017 --> 00:26:45,478
through you, rather than me.

359
00:26:47,772 --> 00:26:49,149
What are you talking about?

360
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:51,901
Make it simple for me to understand.

361
00:26:51,985 --> 00:26:53,737
Didn't you see her smile earlier?

362
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:57,282
She rarely smiles like that.

363
00:27:07,334 --> 00:27:08,752
How does she usually smile?

364
00:27:19,763 --> 00:27:21,765
Hi everyone, I'm Baek Ah-jin.

365
00:27:23,850 --> 00:27:26,770
Today is my first shoot with Dazy.

366
00:27:26,853 --> 00:27:29,606
Fashionable and trendy style...

367
00:27:41,868 --> 00:27:43,995
He didn't stand out at first.

368
00:27:44,454 --> 00:27:47,540
But he took off after being
a substitute host on a music show.

369
00:27:47,624 --> 00:27:48,625
HEO IN-GANG WINS AT BLUEDRAGON AWARDS

370
00:27:48,708 --> 00:27:51,419
Then he switched to acting,
met Longstar's CEO, Seo Mi-ri

371
00:27:51,503 --> 00:27:52,671
and became a star.

372
00:27:53,672 --> 00:27:55,131
Maybe because
he's been working nonstop

373
00:27:55,215 --> 00:27:58,510
he's dealing with depression,
panic disorder, and maybe alcoholism.

374
00:27:59,636 --> 00:28:04,557
He still feels guilty about that
substitute host gig from years ago.

375
00:28:06,309 --> 00:28:08,311
He must think he's being punished.

376
00:28:09,396 --> 00:28:11,648
Both his parents died
when he was little.

377
00:28:11,731 --> 00:28:14,651
His dad died in a car accident
when he was eight.

378
00:28:14,734 --> 00:28:16,319
A year later,
on his dad's memorial day

379
00:28:16,403 --> 00:28:17,612
his mom took her own life.

380
00:28:18,071 --> 00:28:21,116
He and his younger brother were
raised by their maternal grandmother.

381
00:28:21,199 --> 00:28:22,659
I LOVE YOU, GRANDMA
I MISS YOU

382
00:28:23,076 --> 00:28:25,120
He's still really close to her.

383
00:28:26,746 --> 00:28:29,332
He always goes to his grandma's
on days off.

384
00:28:31,084 --> 00:28:34,254
No matter how tired he is,
he always answers her calls.

385
00:28:37,757 --> 00:28:39,134
Kitty.

386
00:28:39,217 --> 00:28:41,219
Why did you come alone?

387
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,346
It's well-known among his fans.

388
00:28:44,597 --> 00:28:46,474
For In-gang, his grandma is

389
00:28:46,975 --> 00:28:48,268
the only real anchor.

390
00:28:50,103 --> 00:28:52,397
NAME: HONG KYUNG-SUK,
HOME: K APARTMENT, YEONDU-DONG

391
00:28:57,444 --> 00:28:59,529
MY DAUGHTER EUN-A'S FAVORITE FOOD
MY GRANDSONS' FAVORITE FOOD

392
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:05,160
IN-GANG WILL BE ON TV TONIGHT
AS AN AWARD SHOW HOST, EUN-A

393
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:07,912
CLAPPING
HAND EXERCISES

394
00:29:07,996 --> 00:29:13,084
HUMAN BEINGS EVENTUALLY
GROW UP IN LONELINESS

395
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:14,711
VOLUNTEER WORK

396
00:29:14,794 --> 00:29:17,380
VISIT EUNGWAN TEMPLE
ON THE DAY OF THE FULL MOON

397
00:29:24,471 --> 00:29:26,514
THE SPIRIT OF THE LATE LIM SUN-YE

398
00:29:58,087 --> 00:30:00,924
I've never seen anyone
come alone to perform memorial rites.

399
00:30:01,007 --> 00:30:02,383
Maybe she has no family.

400
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:04,761
I heard she's an actress.

401
00:30:04,844 --> 00:30:06,805
- An up-and-comer, they say.
- Yes.

402
00:30:06,888 --> 00:30:09,224
She's mostly in films,
so we wouldn't know.

403
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:10,600
I see.

404
00:30:13,102 --> 00:30:15,104
Yesterday's move
must have been rough.

405
00:30:15,188 --> 00:30:17,732
Yes, I haven't even
finished unpacking.

406
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:19,651
Thanks for finding me the place.

407
00:30:20,235 --> 00:30:21,903
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

408
00:30:21,986 --> 00:30:23,947
It's close to the office
and super nice.

409
00:30:26,032 --> 00:30:28,034
Tell me if you need anything else.

410
00:30:28,117 --> 00:30:30,328
I'll bring it as a housewarming gift.

411
00:30:31,955 --> 00:30:35,166
JINSIU RICE CAKE

412
00:30:44,008 --> 00:30:45,009
Hey, Ah-jin.

413
00:30:45,927 --> 00:30:47,262
Goodness.

414
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:48,513
Wait.

415
00:30:48,596 --> 00:30:49,931
What's all this?

416
00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:51,516
Sorry.

417
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:55,728
I ordered by text when I was busy
and typed the wrong number.

418
00:30:56,521 --> 00:30:58,940
This is a four-story building.
I'll give these out on the top floor.

419
00:31:00,650 --> 00:31:03,903
Promise me you won't tell Ms. Seo.

420
00:31:04,445 --> 00:31:06,281
I promise. Let's go inside.

421
00:31:09,242 --> 00:31:14,914
HOME: UNIT 401, BUILDING B,
K APARTMENT, YEONDU-DONG

422
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:38,521
Hello.

423
00:31:38,605 --> 00:31:41,733
I just moved in downstairs
and brought some rice cakes.

424
00:31:41,816 --> 00:31:43,735
Oh, my. Thank you.

425
00:31:44,235 --> 00:31:46,571
What a sweet young lady.

426
00:31:47,155 --> 00:31:49,490
Not at all. I hope you enjoy them.

427
00:31:50,241 --> 00:31:54,621
Did you happen to visit
Eungwan Temple not long ago?

428
00:31:55,413 --> 00:31:57,248
Yes, I did.

429
00:31:57,332 --> 00:31:59,459
What a nice surprise.

430
00:31:59,542 --> 00:32:00,877
We meet again.

431
00:32:02,045 --> 00:32:03,296
Do you live here?

432
00:32:03,379 --> 00:32:05,965
No, a friend of mine just moved in.

433
00:32:09,469 --> 00:32:12,513
Do you have time?

434
00:32:13,264 --> 00:32:15,934
Today's the day my daughter visits

435
00:32:16,017 --> 00:32:18,937
so I cooked way too much.

436
00:32:19,896 --> 00:32:23,983
If it's not a bother,
would you come in for a quick meal?

437
00:32:29,405 --> 00:32:30,573
Yes, Grandma.

438
00:32:30,657 --> 00:32:31,991
I'm on my way now.

439
00:32:33,034 --> 00:32:34,702
Aunt might be late.

440
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:36,454
Did you cook a feast again?

441
00:32:38,623 --> 00:32:40,959
I told you not to wear yourself out.

442
00:32:43,711 --> 00:32:44,712
What?

443
00:32:45,046 --> 00:32:47,006
Who's at your place?

444
00:32:53,721 --> 00:32:56,891
It's my daughter's memorial today.

445
00:32:59,227 --> 00:33:01,562
She was in such a hurry
to leave this world

446
00:33:01,646 --> 00:33:03,564
that she went before me.

447
00:33:04,607 --> 00:33:06,567
It's the one day in a year she comes

448
00:33:07,151 --> 00:33:10,113
so I made all her favorite dishes

449
00:33:10,196 --> 00:33:12,031
and I overdid it again.

450
00:33:12,115 --> 00:33:13,616
Oh, dear.

451
00:33:14,367 --> 00:33:15,660
Thank you for the food.

452
00:33:17,537 --> 00:33:18,705
Help yourself.

453
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:35,221
What's wrong?

454
00:33:35,304 --> 00:33:37,265
There's nothing you like?

455
00:33:55,950 --> 00:33:57,035
Ah-jin.

456
00:33:58,661 --> 00:33:59,704
Step outside.

457
00:33:59,787 --> 00:34:01,080
In-gang, what are you doing?

458
00:34:01,164 --> 00:34:02,457
Don't be rude to a guest.

459
00:34:08,963 --> 00:34:10,256
Get up.

460
00:34:16,971 --> 00:34:18,848
In-gang!

461
00:34:31,027 --> 00:34:32,236
What's this?

462
00:34:33,196 --> 00:34:35,239
Is this really
the kind of person you are?

463
00:34:36,824 --> 00:34:37,992
In-gang.

464
00:34:38,284 --> 00:34:40,328
There's been a misunderstanding.

465
00:34:40,411 --> 00:34:42,371
- She and I met by chance--
- By chance?

466
00:34:44,290 --> 00:34:46,501
You're unbelievable.

467
00:34:49,504 --> 00:34:51,380
What did I do wrong?

468
00:34:52,465 --> 00:34:54,801
I don't see why you're so angry.

469
00:34:54,884 --> 00:34:55,885
You seriously don't?

470
00:34:57,345 --> 00:34:58,471
Then explain it.

471
00:35:00,723 --> 00:35:04,143
Why are you in my grandma's house,
and with what intention?

472
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:13,903
Hyang-i moved in here.

473
00:35:14,987 --> 00:35:17,365
I came to help her
hand out rice cakes

474
00:35:17,698 --> 00:35:19,117
and ended up going inside.

475
00:35:19,951 --> 00:35:22,245
I had no idea
it was your grandma's place.

476
00:35:24,372 --> 00:35:25,873
Do I need to explain more?

477
00:35:27,375 --> 00:35:28,376
So, you didn't know?

478
00:35:30,169 --> 00:35:31,796
All of this was a coincidence?

479
00:35:33,214 --> 00:35:35,383
- You expect me to believe that?
- I'm sorry

480
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:38,886
but your grandma invited me first.

481
00:35:39,679 --> 00:35:41,681
She said she cooked a lot
for her daughter's memorial

482
00:35:41,764 --> 00:35:42,849
and asked me to join.

483
00:35:43,391 --> 00:35:44,851
How could I say no?

484
00:35:45,893 --> 00:35:48,146
I guess you don't care
about her opinion at all.

485
00:35:48,229 --> 00:35:49,897
I don't want to hear anymore. Go.

486
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:52,024
Leave.

487
00:35:56,362 --> 00:35:58,156
At least one thing's clear.

488
00:36:00,992 --> 00:36:02,827
You're still haunted.

489
00:36:06,289 --> 00:36:07,290
What?

490
00:36:09,167 --> 00:36:11,794
The advice you gave me last time.

491
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:15,923
You told me to stop torturing myself.

492
00:36:19,177 --> 00:36:21,971
But you're the one tightening
the noose around your neck.

493
00:36:25,308 --> 00:36:27,727
The one who's overstepping
and tormenting me

494
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:30,271
is you.

495
00:36:34,108 --> 00:36:36,903
Then what did you mean
when you said that to me?

496
00:36:38,321 --> 00:36:42,783
You exposed your flaws
to give me advice

497
00:36:43,242 --> 00:36:44,702
so I mistook it for something more.

498
00:36:46,454 --> 00:36:48,539
Why would you push me away like that?

499
00:36:49,373 --> 00:36:50,416
I guess...

500
00:36:51,417 --> 00:36:53,669
that's how you've lived
your whole life.

501
00:36:58,716 --> 00:37:00,259
Are you saying I'm the one at fault?

502
00:37:03,679 --> 00:37:05,765
Do you know
what people say about you?

503
00:37:08,309 --> 00:37:09,518
That you'll die soon.

504
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:13,606
That you look lonely and on edge.

505
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:18,069
They act concerned behind your back

506
00:37:18,152 --> 00:37:19,737
but no one has the guts to tell you.

507
00:37:21,322 --> 00:37:22,406
But I...

508
00:37:24,617 --> 00:37:26,535
genuinely worry about you.

509
00:37:28,663 --> 00:37:31,290
You look unstable,
so I can't pretend I don't see it.

510
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:37,213
I didn't ask you to.

511
00:37:39,882 --> 00:37:41,634
Don't show up in front of me again.

512
00:37:45,554 --> 00:37:46,806
I really liked you...

513
00:37:49,058 --> 00:37:50,810
as a person

514
00:37:50,893 --> 00:37:52,395
and respected you as an actor.

515
00:37:55,731 --> 00:37:57,191
I guess I was wrong.

516
00:37:59,986 --> 00:38:01,654
You're nothing but a coward.

517
00:38:12,290 --> 00:38:15,126
Anyway, I'm sorry
for causing a misunderstanding.

518
00:38:15,209 --> 00:38:16,335
That's on me.

519
00:38:18,671 --> 00:38:19,755
I apologize.

520
00:38:42,695 --> 00:38:45,156
Isn't it time you told me your plan?

521
00:38:45,740 --> 00:38:48,200
What are you trying to do
with Heo In-gang?

522
00:38:48,576 --> 00:38:49,702
Jun-seo.

523
00:38:50,411 --> 00:38:53,205
I told you. I'm going to date him.

524
00:38:58,753 --> 00:39:01,797
I thought I've done enough
for two years, but I was wrong.

525
00:39:05,009 --> 00:39:06,052
You know

526
00:39:07,094 --> 00:39:09,180
how anxious I am right now.

527
00:39:15,561 --> 00:39:18,189
And Heo In-gang is

528
00:39:19,065 --> 00:39:22,109
just a step that I need
in my current situation.

529
00:39:22,651 --> 00:39:25,279
A lovely set of steps

530
00:39:25,654 --> 00:39:27,323
that will help me get to the top.

531
00:39:45,132 --> 00:39:47,093
THE SPIRITS OF THE LATE
MS. KIM AND MR. HEO

532
00:40:57,663 --> 00:40:59,498
I told you not to let
just anyone in here.

533
00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:01,083
Why don't you ever listen?

534
00:41:01,167 --> 00:41:02,460
She was my guest.

535
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,253
Even if I'm old

536
00:41:04,336 --> 00:41:07,256
I can still tell
who's approaching me with a purpose.

537
00:41:07,339 --> 00:41:09,175
You made a big mistake today.

538
00:41:09,508 --> 00:41:11,969
Apologize when you see
that young lady again.

539
00:41:12,052 --> 00:41:13,095
You're wrong.

540
00:41:14,180 --> 00:41:16,599
There are so many dangerous people
in this line of work.

541
00:41:17,183 --> 00:41:18,350
You have no idea.

542
00:41:19,226 --> 00:41:20,478
You know what?

543
00:41:20,853 --> 00:41:22,813
Heo In-gang blew up at me today.

544
00:41:23,522 --> 00:41:27,026
He grilled me about whether
I approached his grandma on purpose.

545
00:41:32,990 --> 00:41:34,825
To be honest, it was annoying.

546
00:41:35,951 --> 00:41:38,412
My original plan was
to meet his grandma only.

547
00:41:39,663 --> 00:41:42,917
I lost my temper
and said whatever came to mind

548
00:41:43,584 --> 00:41:45,377
and his face changed.

549
00:41:46,128 --> 00:41:47,463
I wonder

550
00:41:47,546 --> 00:41:48,923
which part of what I said

551
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:52,426
touched his heart.

552
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:56,388
Did it make him sad

553
00:41:57,765 --> 00:41:59,058
or surprised?

554
00:42:03,562 --> 00:42:06,065
Grandma, I'm heading out.

555
00:42:10,319 --> 00:42:11,946
Take this with you.

556
00:42:14,949 --> 00:42:18,911
I should have put myself
in your shoes.

557
00:42:19,245 --> 00:42:20,287
I'm sorry.

558
00:42:20,996 --> 00:42:24,875
But you can't go through life
being too calculating

559
00:42:25,209 --> 00:42:27,253
and pushing people away.

560
00:42:28,045 --> 00:42:29,129
Well, you know...

561
00:42:30,172 --> 00:42:32,049
I'm at the end of the road

562
00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:35,970
but you kids have a long way to go.

563
00:42:36,053 --> 00:42:37,638
In the end

564
00:42:37,721 --> 00:42:39,765
you'll have to lean on other people.

565
00:42:44,979 --> 00:42:45,980
Just

566
00:42:46,772 --> 00:42:49,817
listen to your heart and follow it.

567
00:42:54,238 --> 00:42:55,239
I will.

568
00:43:33,485 --> 00:43:34,862
Today was a win.

569
00:43:35,988 --> 00:43:40,200
I'll find out how he reacts
tomorrow or the next day.

570
00:43:41,994 --> 00:43:43,162
I can't wait.

571
00:43:49,126 --> 00:43:50,127
Ah-jin.

572
00:43:52,546 --> 00:43:54,214
Don't worry, Jun-seo.

573
00:43:54,673 --> 00:43:56,467
I'll date him for exactly a year.

574
00:43:57,551 --> 00:43:58,969
That's all I need.

575
00:44:15,903 --> 00:44:17,905
GEUMHWADANG BAKERY CAFÉ

576
00:44:24,536 --> 00:44:28,374
Director Sung suggested
that we meet here, so I said okay.

577
00:44:30,250 --> 00:44:31,543
Are you sure you're fine?

578
00:44:32,211 --> 00:44:33,837
I'm fine. Who cares?

579
00:44:40,761 --> 00:44:42,429
- We'll meet again next time.
- Sure.

580
00:44:43,055 --> 00:44:44,056
Take care.

581
00:44:44,057 --> 00:44:54,907
Officail Website : kissasian.be  Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

582
00:44:44,932 --> 00:44:45,974
In-gang.

583
00:44:49,144 --> 00:44:53,190
I booked Geumhwadang like you asked

584
00:44:54,024 --> 00:44:55,818
but I'm not sure about this.

585
00:44:55,901 --> 00:44:57,111
Thanks for your work.

586
00:44:57,528 --> 00:44:59,238
Anyway, I did as you asked.

587
00:44:59,697 --> 00:45:02,574
Even if anything goes wrong,
leave me out of it.

588
00:45:03,701 --> 00:45:05,703
I'll handle whatever comes.

589
00:45:05,786 --> 00:45:07,579
Don't you worry.

590
00:45:28,308 --> 00:45:29,685
This is our new dessert.

591
00:45:29,768 --> 00:45:30,811
Try it.

592
00:45:36,942 --> 00:45:39,069
It took a lot of trial and error
to nail the taste.

593
00:45:39,153 --> 00:45:40,946
It reminded me of our trainee days.

594
00:45:41,029 --> 00:45:43,574
I thought being an idol singer
was the toughest job back then

595
00:45:43,657 --> 00:45:45,284
but once I lived another life

596
00:45:45,784 --> 00:45:47,619
I realized that nothing was easy.

597
00:45:48,495 --> 00:45:50,706
- Are you doing well?
- Of course.

598
00:45:52,166 --> 00:45:53,751
That's why I came to see you.

599
00:45:54,293 --> 00:45:55,669
And I had something to say.

600
00:45:57,379 --> 00:45:59,631
I actually knew it back then.

601
00:46:01,383 --> 00:46:03,719
That the macarons had nuts inside.

602
00:46:05,679 --> 00:46:08,557
And I knew you saw it
and said nothing.

603
00:46:09,933 --> 00:46:10,934
But you know what?

604
00:46:11,727 --> 00:46:13,854
I ate them on purpose
from the first place.

605
00:46:15,272 --> 00:46:16,732
Because I was living in hell.

606
00:46:18,776 --> 00:46:22,905
The music on stage
made it hard to breathe.

607
00:46:23,447 --> 00:46:26,366
I felt like I'd die if I didn't quit.

608
00:46:27,117 --> 00:46:28,118
So, I ate them

609
00:46:28,786 --> 00:46:31,121
knowing they had nuts in them.

610
00:46:31,830 --> 00:46:35,709
So, stop carrying guilt
about stepping in

611
00:46:37,294 --> 00:46:38,712
as a substitute host that day.

612
00:46:40,964 --> 00:46:42,925
Is this some sudden confession?

613
00:46:44,009 --> 00:46:47,095
I knew my messages
would make you suffer.

614
00:46:47,513 --> 00:46:49,681
So, I'm sorry
for sending them anyway.

615
00:46:50,724 --> 00:46:52,392
I'm getting married soon.

616
00:46:52,476 --> 00:46:54,311
I'm more at peace than ever.

617
00:46:55,354 --> 00:46:56,355
Maybe it's time...

618
00:46:57,898 --> 00:46:59,483
you let go.

619
00:47:04,154 --> 00:47:05,197
No, In-gang.

620
00:47:06,156 --> 00:47:07,199
Calm down.

621
00:47:18,293 --> 00:47:19,670
Was her name Baek Ah-jin?

622
00:47:20,087 --> 00:47:21,630
She came to see me.

623
00:47:22,172 --> 00:47:23,423
I don't know how she knew

624
00:47:24,258 --> 00:47:25,759
but she asked about back then.

625
00:47:26,385 --> 00:47:29,721
"Does he know
that I knew and said nothing?

626
00:47:29,805 --> 00:47:32,808
Is he getting back at me
by texting me

627
00:47:32,891 --> 00:47:35,686
or does he really wish me well?"

628
00:47:35,769 --> 00:47:38,564
Whichever it is,
both are hell for me.

629
00:47:39,356 --> 00:47:42,359
So, I told her,
and she asked me for help.

630
00:47:42,693 --> 00:47:45,696
She said you were tormented
and that she wanted my help.

631
00:47:46,196 --> 00:47:47,739
She seemed like a good person.

632
00:47:47,823 --> 00:47:49,491
It also looked
like she really cared for you.

633
00:47:53,078 --> 00:47:54,079
I'm sorry.

634
00:48:08,343 --> 00:48:09,469
In-gang, what's wrong?

635
00:48:14,558 --> 00:48:17,978
I went to the awards and shot a drama
with her because you asked

636
00:48:18,312 --> 00:48:20,355
but I don't want to be involved
with Baek Ah-jin anymore.

637
00:48:20,981 --> 00:48:24,067
You never complained,
whatever the gig was.

638
00:48:24,651 --> 00:48:26,445
But this one bothers you?

639
00:48:27,696 --> 00:48:28,697
Why?

640
00:48:28,989 --> 00:48:30,574
Did she make a mistake?

641
00:48:31,033 --> 00:48:34,036
Somehow, she keeps overstepping.
It makes me uncomfortable.

642
00:48:34,119 --> 00:48:36,788
And I broke up with Lena for good,
so put out the breakup news soon.

643
00:48:38,624 --> 00:48:39,666
Got it.

644
00:48:40,876 --> 00:48:41,960
Thanks.

645
00:48:42,044 --> 00:48:44,046
No need to thank me. That's a given.

646
00:48:53,096 --> 00:48:55,265
Actors Heo In-gang and Lena
have ended

647
00:48:55,349 --> 00:48:57,768
their public relationship
after a year.

648
00:48:57,851 --> 00:49:00,562
Their agency, Longstar Entertainment

649
00:49:00,854 --> 00:49:03,857
said their busy schedules
created distance

650
00:49:03,941 --> 00:49:07,235
and they decided to return
to being colleagues.

651
00:49:07,319 --> 00:49:09,780
Many fans are disappointed

652
00:49:09,863 --> 00:49:12,115
as the two were seen
as a great match.

653
00:49:13,742 --> 00:49:15,035
What are you doing?

654
00:49:15,118 --> 00:49:17,829
Are you even looking into it?
Why is it taking so long?

655
00:49:19,331 --> 00:49:21,500
And stop whining!

656
00:49:24,002 --> 00:49:25,754
Don't you realize
the monthly support I give you

657
00:49:25,837 --> 00:49:27,297
is more than your salary?

658
00:49:27,381 --> 00:49:29,841
Do your job right before I fire you.

659
00:49:30,842 --> 00:49:32,135
Damn it.

660
00:49:33,595 --> 00:49:34,596
That bitch...

661
00:49:35,847 --> 00:49:36,974
Goddamn it!

662
00:49:47,526 --> 00:49:48,568
It's me.

663
00:49:49,027 --> 00:49:51,154
The materials we discussed are ready.

664
00:49:51,738 --> 00:49:53,865
Can we meet where we did last time?

665
00:49:53,949 --> 00:49:54,950
In about an hour.

666
00:49:55,867 --> 00:49:56,868
Okay.

667
00:50:12,300 --> 00:50:13,385
Gosh.

668
00:50:15,637 --> 00:50:17,097
You're that guy from before.

669
00:50:17,180 --> 00:50:18,223
So what?

670
00:50:18,306 --> 00:50:20,434
- Happy to see me?
- Yeah, sure.

671
00:50:20,851 --> 00:50:23,729
How dare you do this
in broad daylight--

672
00:50:24,938 --> 00:50:28,442
You took bribes to bury a case
when you were on the narcotics squad.

673
00:50:28,525 --> 00:50:31,528
My life's already in the gutter!

674
00:50:31,611 --> 00:50:33,613
But it's a different story
with a celebrity.

675
00:50:33,697 --> 00:50:37,617
One word from me, and Baek Ah-jin
will disappear without a--

676
00:50:40,162 --> 00:50:43,290
Your daughter
did drugs in the States.

677
00:50:45,459 --> 00:50:47,669
Try burying that one, too.

678
00:50:47,753 --> 00:50:49,546
PERSONAL DETAILS

679
00:50:51,757 --> 00:50:53,300
PARK DAE-HO

680
00:50:56,219 --> 00:50:58,096
The suspicions about Baek Ah-jin

681
00:50:58,180 --> 00:51:00,098
in the Nojeong-dong murder case
aren't true.

682
00:51:00,182 --> 00:51:01,641
There's no file.

683
00:51:02,309 --> 00:51:04,811
The person you've called
can't be reached--

684
00:51:04,895 --> 00:51:06,271
Shit.

685
00:51:06,980 --> 00:51:08,648
She probably got to him first.

686
00:51:08,732 --> 00:51:09,941
I told you so.

687
00:51:10,025 --> 00:51:12,027
She's not an easy target.

688
00:51:12,110 --> 00:51:13,403
This won't be simple.

689
00:51:13,487 --> 00:51:16,073
That's what amateurs say.

690
00:51:16,156 --> 00:51:18,867
I wire you ten million won
every month

691
00:51:18,950 --> 00:51:21,912
but all you do is
leave a few comments on my articles.

692
00:51:21,995 --> 00:51:23,455
Aren't you taking it a bit too far?

693
00:51:23,538 --> 00:51:26,500
Don't get touchy
about hearing this from your cousin.

694
00:51:26,583 --> 00:51:28,794
It's not a small amount
to let pride get in the way.

695
00:51:30,128 --> 00:51:33,507
Also, don't you dare
whine in front of me again.

696
00:51:34,716 --> 00:51:36,051
Earn

697
00:51:37,177 --> 00:51:38,345
what you're paid.

698
00:51:39,638 --> 00:51:41,598
That reporter
Lieutenant Park was trying to contact

699
00:51:42,849 --> 00:51:44,684
only writes hit pieces on Boss.

700
00:51:46,561 --> 00:51:47,604
Lim Hee-kook?

701
00:51:47,938 --> 00:51:49,439
Yes, that's his name.

702
00:51:49,523 --> 00:51:52,943
He writes nothing but good things
about Lena or something.

703
00:51:53,026 --> 00:51:55,695
It turns out they're related.

704
00:51:57,656 --> 00:51:59,741
I'll talk to Lena.

705
00:52:01,660 --> 00:52:02,661
What?

706
00:52:03,245 --> 00:52:04,663
You know her?

707
00:52:04,746 --> 00:52:07,290
I hear she's been bullying Ah-jin.

708
00:52:07,374 --> 00:52:08,375
What?

709
00:52:08,458 --> 00:52:10,794
Jeez, she's unhinged.

710
00:52:10,877 --> 00:52:13,171
Why keep poking Ah-jin
when she's done nothing?

711
00:52:15,924 --> 00:52:18,885
By the way,
Ah-jin says she'll date him.

712
00:52:19,719 --> 00:52:20,720
Is that true?

713
00:52:20,804 --> 00:52:22,514
That's her next move.

714
00:52:22,597 --> 00:52:24,349
I thought you two were
into each other.

715
00:52:30,397 --> 00:52:31,773
You're pathetic.

716
00:52:32,149 --> 00:52:33,233
If I were you...

717
00:52:36,361 --> 00:52:37,362
You know what?

718
00:52:38,572 --> 00:52:39,614
Forget it.

719
00:52:43,243 --> 00:52:44,786
Man.

720
00:52:53,795 --> 00:52:55,213
Oh, how did you...

721
00:52:56,131 --> 00:52:59,843
I couldn't get you off my mind
after that night.

722
00:53:00,719 --> 00:53:02,012
Take a seat.

723
00:53:06,183 --> 00:53:08,101
I should have come to you first.

724
00:53:08,185 --> 00:53:09,853
I wanted to apologize.

725
00:53:11,062 --> 00:53:13,273
And to see you again.

726
00:53:14,316 --> 00:53:15,650
I'm sorry.

727
00:53:15,734 --> 00:53:17,819
My boy has been hurt before.

728
00:53:18,153 --> 00:53:21,364
I told him not to do that.

729
00:53:21,740 --> 00:53:23,033
Please don't hold it against him.

730
00:53:24,951 --> 00:53:26,786
He lost his parents in his childhood

731
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:29,164
and I raised him.

732
00:53:30,207 --> 00:53:31,208
Yes, I know.

733
00:53:34,169 --> 00:53:35,420
I understand.

734
00:53:36,129 --> 00:53:40,342
I also lost my parents
when I was little.

735
00:53:40,759 --> 00:53:43,261
Oh, I see.

736
00:53:45,597 --> 00:53:49,392
But can I ask you something?

737
00:53:49,768 --> 00:53:51,061
Of course.

738
00:53:51,436 --> 00:53:54,272
Why did you cry that night?

739
00:53:58,526 --> 00:54:02,697
Because it reminded me
of my late mom.

740
00:54:03,823 --> 00:54:08,161
She used to love spring greens.

741
00:54:08,245 --> 00:54:10,455
MY DAUGHTER EUN-A'S FAVORITE FOOD
SPRING GREENS, FRESH KIMCHI...

742
00:54:14,584 --> 00:54:16,253
Sorry, I can't stop myself.

743
00:54:17,045 --> 00:54:19,130
Please don't worry
about what happened.

744
00:54:33,186 --> 00:54:34,688
Don't worry, Jun-seo.

745
00:54:35,647 --> 00:54:37,524
I'll date him for exactly a year.

746
00:54:38,775 --> 00:54:40,151
Don't go.

747
00:54:47,284 --> 00:54:48,660
Just stay with me.

748
00:54:50,537 --> 00:54:52,205
That's all I need.

749
00:55:08,221 --> 00:55:10,390
Do you know
what people say about you?

750
00:55:11,099 --> 00:55:12,267
That you'll die soon.

751
00:55:19,524 --> 00:55:21,276
That you look lonely and on edge.

752
00:55:22,152 --> 00:55:24,029
I genuinely worry about you.

753
00:55:24,571 --> 00:55:25,989
I didn't ask you to.

754
00:55:26,698 --> 00:55:28,074
I really liked you

755
00:55:28,491 --> 00:55:30,452
as a person

756
00:55:30,535 --> 00:55:31,870
and respected you as an actor.

757
00:55:31,953 --> 00:55:33,371
I guess I was wrong.

758
00:55:38,960 --> 00:55:40,503
You're nothing but a coward.

759
00:55:49,220 --> 00:55:50,805
You'll stay with me, right?

760
00:55:53,683 --> 00:55:55,727
Don't ever leave me again.

761
00:56:11,201 --> 00:56:12,827
I'm sorry about the other day.

762
00:56:12,911 --> 00:56:14,746
How about dinner tonight?

763
00:56:23,797 --> 00:56:25,965
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE OTHER DAY
HOW ABOUT DINNER TONIGHT?

764
00:56:41,481 --> 00:56:43,733
I'll be free around nine o'clock.

765
00:56:43,817 --> 00:56:45,151
How about Pavilion?

766
00:56:54,077 --> 00:56:55,078
No way.

767
00:56:56,371 --> 00:56:57,414
It's Ah-jin.

768
00:57:05,630 --> 00:57:07,382
Gosh.

769
00:57:07,465 --> 00:57:11,261
Kim Jae-oh is a big shot now,
visiting a celebrity's place.

770
00:57:16,182 --> 00:57:17,392
What's with the suit?

771
00:57:18,268 --> 00:57:19,436
Where were you?

772
00:57:19,853 --> 00:57:22,021
My brother's graduation.

773
00:57:22,105 --> 00:57:26,359
Shouldn't you be eating with him
instead of coming here?

774
00:57:27,652 --> 00:57:29,070
I wish I could

775
00:57:30,488 --> 00:57:31,948
but he won't see me.

776
00:57:34,200 --> 00:57:35,201
Well...

777
00:57:37,328 --> 00:57:38,329
I get it, though.

778
00:57:39,164 --> 00:57:40,165
Why?

779
00:57:40,999 --> 00:57:42,333
Because you're a murderer?

780
00:57:48,047 --> 00:57:49,257
Your brother is an idiot.

781
00:57:49,716 --> 00:57:52,010
I would have kept you close.

782
00:57:52,677 --> 00:57:53,761
Am I wrong?

783
00:57:54,262 --> 00:57:55,889
A brother who would do
anything for me.

784
00:57:56,222 --> 00:57:57,682
I'd stick with him for life.

785
00:57:58,308 --> 00:57:59,851
Your brother's a fool.

786
00:58:05,607 --> 00:58:08,818
You're definitely something else.

787
00:58:08,902 --> 00:58:09,903
You really are.

788
00:58:11,029 --> 00:58:14,574
But for the record,
he's smart as hell.

789
00:58:14,949 --> 00:58:16,659
His grades are amazing.

790
00:58:17,827 --> 00:58:19,162
He's nothing like me.

791
00:58:24,918 --> 00:58:25,919
So, why am I here?

792
00:58:26,669 --> 00:58:27,712
What's up?

793
00:58:27,795 --> 00:58:29,130
Jae-oh.

794
00:58:29,214 --> 00:58:30,840
Can I ask you a favor?

795
00:58:31,466 --> 00:58:33,927
Of course, anything for you.

796
01:00:11,691 --> 01:00:12,692
Shit.

797
01:00:13,526 --> 01:00:16,779
Who turns the wheel like that
out of nowhere?

798
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:18,573
Are you okay?

799
01:00:18,656 --> 01:00:21,993
Call Longstar, and they'll handle it.
I'm in a bit of a hurry.

800
01:00:22,076 --> 01:00:23,161
Hold up.

801
01:00:23,995 --> 01:00:24,996
You're a celebrity.

802
01:00:25,580 --> 01:00:28,875
You are. Right, you're Heo...

803
01:00:28,958 --> 01:00:30,168
Heo.

804
01:00:30,418 --> 01:00:31,794
Gosh.

805
01:00:31,878 --> 01:00:34,213
I've never met a celeb in real life.

806
01:00:34,297 --> 01:00:36,758
I thought you'd be crazy handsome.

807
01:00:38,092 --> 01:00:39,302
Not so impressive, though.

808
01:00:42,305 --> 01:00:43,973
Your tire's blown.

809
01:00:45,016 --> 01:00:46,684
Wait, wow.

810
01:00:46,768 --> 01:00:49,604
Jeez, this is bad.

811
01:00:52,398 --> 01:00:56,027
Anyway, it looks
like I'm partly at fault.

812
01:00:58,112 --> 01:00:59,822
Even my phone's cracked.

813
01:01:00,573 --> 01:01:03,201
Let me borrow your phone
to call the insurance.

814
01:01:03,826 --> 01:01:05,828
No, it's fine. I'm late.

815
01:01:05,912 --> 01:01:06,996
Stop.

816
01:01:07,497 --> 01:01:08,790
Where do you think you're going?

817
01:01:08,873 --> 01:01:12,085
You're going to call the police
and say I'm a hit-and-run, right?

818
01:01:12,168 --> 01:01:13,628
I won't.

819
01:01:14,087 --> 01:01:15,505
And I won't charge you
for the repair.

820
01:01:15,588 --> 01:01:16,923
You can just go.

821
01:01:20,176 --> 01:01:22,053
Stall him as long as you can.

822
01:01:22,136 --> 01:01:23,763
Whatever it takes.

823
01:01:23,846 --> 01:01:26,766
Just make sure
he's late to the restaurant.

824
01:01:45,451 --> 01:01:47,870
Come on. Just let me use your phone.

825
01:01:47,954 --> 01:01:49,080
Jeez.

826
01:01:56,504 --> 01:01:57,755
I didn't do it.

827
01:01:58,506 --> 01:02:01,467
I was just holding it,
and you knocked it out.

828
01:02:01,551 --> 01:02:02,760
- Got it?
- Seriously.

829
01:02:04,220 --> 01:02:06,723
What do we do now?

830
01:02:06,806 --> 01:02:08,224
Shoot.

831
01:02:29,454 --> 01:02:31,038
What's gotten into you?

832
01:02:32,707 --> 01:02:34,250
You called me first.

833
01:02:36,544 --> 01:02:38,254
I figured you could use a friend.

834
01:02:39,422 --> 01:02:42,133
You don't strike me
as someone with a big circle.

835
01:02:44,927 --> 01:02:46,429
What's the truth

836
01:02:47,221 --> 01:02:48,473
with you and Ah-jin?

837
01:02:49,265 --> 01:02:50,349
Be honest.

838
01:02:52,018 --> 01:02:53,311
When we were kids

839
01:02:54,979 --> 01:02:56,606
our parents remarried

840
01:02:57,690 --> 01:03:00,109
and we lived together briefly.
She's my younger sister.

841
01:03:01,819 --> 01:03:02,945
"Oh, I see.

842
01:03:03,696 --> 01:03:05,656
She was your sister."

843
01:03:06,407 --> 01:03:07,950
Did you expect me to say that?

844
01:03:08,618 --> 01:03:09,952
Please.

845
01:03:11,579 --> 01:03:14,457
That's not how a man looks
at his little sister.

846
01:03:18,294 --> 01:03:19,337
You got me.

847
01:03:20,755 --> 01:03:21,756
Darn.

848
01:03:24,717 --> 01:03:25,968
So, it's love, huh?

849
01:04:13,182 --> 01:04:14,767
Sir, I'll get off here.

850
01:04:20,231 --> 01:04:22,358
Ma'am, we close at ten o'clock.

851
01:04:22,859 --> 01:04:23,860
Okay.

852
01:05:09,739 --> 01:05:11,616
Isn't that Baek Ah-jin?

853
01:05:12,158 --> 01:05:15,578
Man, her face and body are unreal.

854
01:05:15,661 --> 01:05:17,788
She's the pure and glamorous type.

855
01:05:17,872 --> 01:05:20,583
No wonder guys go crazy.

856
01:05:20,666 --> 01:05:22,793
With a body like that

857
01:05:22,877 --> 01:05:25,963
shouldn't she dress lighter
for the people?

858
01:05:26,047 --> 01:05:28,466
Spend the night with me, girl.

859
01:05:29,133 --> 01:05:30,134
Wait, who are--

860
01:05:33,679 --> 01:05:34,764
In-gang.

861
01:05:38,976 --> 01:05:40,061
You piece of--

862
01:05:44,982 --> 01:05:46,734
Come here. Let go.

863
01:05:46,817 --> 01:05:48,361
Fucking let me go!

864
01:05:48,444 --> 01:05:49,487
Come here.

865
01:06:01,165 --> 01:06:02,875
Hey.

866
01:06:02,959 --> 01:06:04,710
Move, hey!

867
01:06:04,794 --> 01:06:06,754
- Get lost!
- What?

868
01:06:06,837 --> 01:06:09,590
Get out of here!

869
01:06:10,049 --> 01:06:12,051
You two are lunatics.

870
01:06:13,678 --> 01:06:16,138
Jun-seo, are you okay?

871
01:06:16,430 --> 01:06:19,183
Jun-seo, wake up.

872
01:06:19,433 --> 01:06:21,310
Have you been waiting
this whole time?

873
01:06:22,103 --> 01:06:24,188
I couldn't reach you,
and I was worried.

874
01:06:24,271 --> 01:06:25,898
I couldn't just leave.

875
01:06:26,440 --> 01:06:27,566
I'm sorry.

876
01:06:27,650 --> 01:06:29,485
I got into a minor accident
on the way.

877
01:06:29,568 --> 01:06:31,862
My phone fell into a sewage

878
01:06:31,946 --> 01:06:33,781
and I couldn't remember your number.

879
01:06:33,864 --> 01:06:36,575
You should have gone home
if you couldn't reach me.

880
01:06:36,909 --> 01:06:38,744
You waited for me
in this freezing weather?

881
01:06:39,620 --> 01:06:41,497
I didn't want to miss you.

882
01:06:42,206 --> 01:06:43,708
You're here now, so it's fine.

883
01:06:48,504 --> 01:06:50,673
By the way,
why are you dressed so lightly?

884
01:06:51,465 --> 01:06:52,591
Aren't you cold?

885
01:07:00,099 --> 01:07:02,810
Wear a scarf next time.

886
01:07:02,893 --> 01:07:06,439
I know it's stuffy,
but it keeps you warm.

887
01:07:10,317 --> 01:07:12,278
Am I nagging?

888
01:07:14,321 --> 01:07:16,282
Is this too much?

889
01:07:38,345 --> 01:07:39,722
Yoon Jun-seo!

890
01:07:44,685 --> 01:07:47,563
You missed me, didn't you?

891
01:08:20,763 --> 01:08:22,556
Hi, I'm Baek Ah-jin.

892
01:08:22,640 --> 01:08:24,100
I'm Yoon Jun-seo.

893
01:08:36,195 --> 01:08:38,614
Jun-seo, help me.

894
01:08:40,783 --> 01:08:42,493
I'm always on your side.

895
01:08:48,916 --> 01:08:50,209
Help me.

896
01:08:55,548 --> 01:08:57,383
I want to learn to love him.

897
01:09:34,920 --> 01:09:39,341
DEAR X

898
01:11:58,897 --> 01:12:00,899
Subtitles by Ho-young Yun
